AIM:- Java Script Events and Event Handlers: 
a) Handling User Interactions Using JavaScript Events and Event Handlers.
Code:-
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<title>JavaScript Events Example</title>

<script>

function showMessage() {
    document.getElementById("result").innerHTML = "Button was clicked!";
}

function changeText() {
    document.getElementById("result").innerHTML = "Mouse moved over the text!";
}

function resetText() {
    document.getElementById("result").innerHTML = "Mouse moved away!";
}

</script>

</head>

<body>

<h2>Handling User Interaction using JavaScript Events</h2>

<button onclick="showMessage()">Click Me</button>
<br><br>

<p onmouseover="changeText()" onmouseout="resetText()">
Move your mouse over this text
</p>

<h3 id="result">Result will appear here</h3>

</body>
</html>

